in military grade weaponry to law enforcement agencies without sufficient need or accountability.

America has a long way to go before it can move past this sad truth, but the national reckoning after George Floyd‚Äôs murder gives hope that we can adapt and change for the better.
If racism is America‚Äôs first original sin, gun violence is a close second. Both have irrevocably defined and shaped our everyday life in countless ways.

As I reflect on the second anniversary of the brutal and gut-wrenching murder of #GeorgeFloyd, my heart is heavy.

This requires Republicans beholden to the gun lobby to step up. 
Then we can begin the long journey towards slowing the occurrence of mass casualty gun violence in our country.
